<CSSGrid-column>
<summary>
The <strong><c>grid-column</c></strong> CSS <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Shorthand_properties">shorthand property</see> specifies a grid item's size and location within a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/grid column">grid column</see> by contributing a line, a span, or nothing (automatic) to its grid placement, thereby specifying the inline-start and inline-end edge of its <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/grid areas">grid areas</see>.
</summary>
